summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Six Hundred Forty-five and 84/100 (645.84) Dollars, or so much thereof as may be necessary from the General Fund of the City of Seattle, to pay the City's portion of the cost of the improvement of Twenty-fifth Avenue South, by constructing sewers therein, as provided for in Ordinance No. 18550, creating Local Improvement District No. 1749.
